tep-by-Step Instructions
Clone the Repository (If Available)

If you have access to a repository where the project is hosted (e.g., GitHub), clone it:

bash

git clone https://github.com/your-repo/capsule-fault-diagnosis.git
cd capsule-fault-diagnosis
Prepare the Dataset

Ensure your dataset is organized as described earlier. You might need to write a custom Dataset class using torch.utils.data.Dataset to load your data.

Set Up the Environment

Ensure all required libraries are installed (as per the Environment Setup section).

Configure Hyperparameters

Adjust hyperparameters like learning rate, batch size, number of epochs, etc., in your training script.

Run Training

bash

python train.py
Run Evaluation

bash

python test.py
Monitor Training

Use tools like TensorBoard or logging libraries to monitor training progress.

Example Project Structure
bash

capsule-fault-diagnosis/
│
├── dataset/
│   ├── train/
│   └── test/
│
├── models/
│   ├── capsule_network.py
│   └── loss.py
│
├── utils/
│   ├── data_loader.py
│   └── utils.py
│
├── train.py
├── test.py
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md
